          Use events for cross-domain communication
        </h3>
        <p class="example-rule-desc">
          When one bounded context needs to react to something in another,
          emit a domain event rather than calling the other context's
          service directly. This keeps domains decoupled and allows new
          consumers to be added without modifying the producer.
        </p>

